WEBVTT

00:07.485 --> 00:10.575
[exciting music]

00:10.662 --> 00:17.539
♪ ♪

01:41.318 --> 01:42.798
[tense music]

01:42.885 --> 01:44.800
- What did you put
on that ship?

01:44.887 --> 01:48.325
- Just as the Federation
ignited our civil war,

01:48.412 --> 01:51.067
when the Protostar comes
into contact

01:51.154 --> 01:52.938
with a Starfleet vessel,

01:53.025 --> 01:56.203
our weapons will release
a signal that will corrupt--

01:56.290 --> 01:58.248
- Corrupt.

01:58.335 --> 01:59.510
Even the way he says it--
- Quiet!

01:59.597 --> 02:01.730
- Shh.

02:01.817 --> 02:04.211
- Turning their ships
against each other

02:04.298 --> 02:08.432
until the entire alliance
is reduced to nothing.

02:08.519 --> 02:10.217
- Our ship will
destroy Starfleet.

02:10.304 --> 02:12.219
Holodeck, playback volume off.

02:12.306 --> 02:14.743
- A secret weapon on my ship?

02:14.830 --> 02:17.876
- That explains why the relay
station destroyed itself,

02:17.963 --> 02:20.749
yet everywhere else we
went was without incident.

02:20.836 --> 02:24.187
- All this 'cause Starfleet
made first contact

02:24.274 --> 02:25.449
with their home world?

02:25.536 --> 02:28.191
- You mean will.
It hasn't happened yet.

02:28.278 --> 02:30.324
My father is from the future.

02:30.411 --> 02:33.153
I mean was.

02:33.240 --> 02:35.111
I know it's a lot to take in.

02:35.198 --> 02:40.116
- [gurgling]

02:40.203 --> 02:43.119
- I think all this time travel
talk is making Murf sick.

02:43.206 --> 02:45.034
- It's impossible.

02:45.121 --> 02:48.168
- He can be indestructible
but not catch a cold?

02:48.255 --> 02:49.691
- I meant the weapon.

02:49.778 --> 02:51.954
I would know if there
was a destructive force

02:52.041 --> 02:54.261
of that magnitude
on board this ship.

02:54.348 --> 02:57.089
- Just like you knew
our ship had a protostar?

02:57.177 --> 02:59.135
Oh, that's right.

02:59.222 --> 03:01.659
They wiped that
from your memory too.

03:01.746 --> 03:03.357
- Touché.

03:03.444 --> 03:05.489
- Ooh!
Computer, end playback.

03:05.576 --> 03:07.926
- Affirmative.

03:08.013 --> 03:09.972
- It's okay, Zero.

03:10.059 --> 03:13.062
- I couldn't live with myself
if I hurt anyone else.

03:13.149 --> 03:14.890
If you'll excuse me.

03:14.977 --> 03:16.544
- Zero, wait--

03:16.631 --> 03:18.589
- Look,
Jankom fully understands

03:18.676 --> 03:20.461
he needs to be sensitive,

03:20.548 --> 03:25.248
but there's a weapon
aboard our ship

03:25.335 --> 03:28.208
that we gotta find!

03:28.295 --> 03:30.645
- Not here!

03:30.732 --> 03:33.561
- We're coming up empty,
in the engine room.

03:33.648 --> 03:35.215
- Not here either.

03:35.302 --> 03:37.565
We've searched every bulkhead,

03:37.652 --> 03:39.001
cargo hold,
and Jefferies tube.

03:39.088 --> 03:41.308
- But not this room.

03:41.395 --> 03:43.005
- Ah!

03:43.092 --> 03:45.050
- Look for panels,
hidden switches,

03:45.137 --> 03:46.661
anything out of place.

03:46.748 --> 03:48.750
- If only we knew what
we were looking for.

03:48.837 --> 03:51.187
Jankom's detecting
tritanium duranium alloys,

03:51.274 --> 03:53.972
transparent aluminum...

03:54.059 --> 03:56.323
Oh, ho-ho!

03:56.410 --> 03:59.021
Uh, guys?

03:59.108 --> 04:01.850
- I don't recall
that being here.

04:01.937 --> 04:03.460
- What is it?

04:03.547 --> 04:06.507
- It's a symbol of Solum.

04:06.594 --> 04:09.031
- Your heirloom, it's reacting.

04:09.118 --> 04:11.207
♪ ♪

04:11.294 --> 04:13.035
- You don't think--

04:13.122 --> 04:15.820
♪ ♪

04:15.907 --> 04:17.909
[floor clanking]
- What?

04:17.996 --> 04:19.998
What?

04:20.085 --> 04:22.044
- How extraordinary.

04:22.131 --> 04:25.221
- I have no record
of this entire sub-deck.

04:25.308 --> 04:29.312
- Huh, Pog'll go last.

04:29.399 --> 04:32.620
You know, to protect you.
[laughs]

04:32.707 --> 04:35.884
[machinery humming]
- What's that humming?

04:35.971 --> 04:39.017
♪ ♪

04:39.104 --> 04:41.977
- Wow.

04:42.064 --> 04:45.633
- That's the weapon
the Diviner was talking about.

04:45.720 --> 04:48.766
- I've never seen
anything like it.

04:48.853 --> 04:51.682
- It's like it's alive.

04:51.769 --> 04:53.771
- Then we need
to make it not alive.

04:53.858 --> 04:55.556
- How about we launch it
out of an airlock?

04:55.643 --> 04:57.514
- But then someone
else may use it.

04:57.601 --> 04:59.168
- Then let's take it apart.

04:59.255 --> 05:01.431
- This is technology
from the future.

05:01.518 --> 05:03.346
You can't just cut a wire.

05:03.433 --> 05:05.174
- At least I'm offering ideas.

05:05.261 --> 05:07.742
- Don't worry.
Jankom will fix it.

05:07.829 --> 05:08.873
- Whoa, no!
No, no, no, no, no.

05:08.960 --> 05:10.397
- Jankom!

05:10.484 --> 05:11.876
♪ ♪

05:11.963 --> 05:13.704
- How curious.
- Wha?

05:13.791 --> 05:15.402
- It protects itself.

05:15.489 --> 05:16.794
- If we can't hurt it,

05:16.881 --> 05:18.579
we need to find a way
to shut it down.

05:18.666 --> 05:20.450
- Starfleet would
know what to do.

05:20.537 --> 05:22.409
- We ain't Starfleet, kid.

05:22.496 --> 05:24.149
[alarm beeping]

05:24.236 --> 05:25.934
- Oh, great.
Now what?

05:26.021 --> 05:28.676
- Proximity alert.
Vessel detected.

05:28.763 --> 05:32.375
- What the--hello.

05:32.462 --> 05:34.986
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
What are we even looking at?

05:35.073 --> 05:37.075
Is that a ship?

05:37.162 --> 05:42.124
♪ ♪

05:42.211 --> 05:44.300
- A Borg Cube.

05:44.387 --> 05:45.519
We must leave at once.

05:45.606 --> 05:47.042
- Hold on.

05:47.129 --> 05:48.957
What's a Borg cube?

05:49.044 --> 05:51.351
- The Borg are a race
of enhanced humanoids,

05:51.438 --> 05:53.875
mindless drones
that assimilate everyone

05:53.962 --> 05:55.616
they come across
into their collective.

05:55.703 --> 05:57.792
- Collective?
They are a hive mind?

05:57.879 --> 06:00.708
- You mean
they all share one brain?

06:00.795 --> 06:02.579
- Thousands of minds
working as one.

06:02.666 --> 06:05.060
- With the sole intent
to eradicate everything

06:05.147 --> 06:07.932
that's perceived to be
a threat, including us.

06:08.019 --> 06:09.543
There's no reasoning
with them.

06:09.630 --> 06:13.111
Any tactic, any measure,
they learn and adapt

06:13.198 --> 06:14.678
until our weapons are useless,
and we are--

06:14.765 --> 06:16.114
- Eradicated?

06:16.201 --> 06:19.422
- Worse.
Until we become one of them.

06:19.509 --> 06:21.685
- No way Jankom flies in a box.

06:21.772 --> 06:23.513
- If we go to warp now,
we just might--

06:23.600 --> 06:25.297
- Wait.

06:25.385 --> 06:28.562
She said they learn and adapt
until our weapons are useless.

06:28.649 --> 06:32.696
What if they know a way to
disarm that thing below deck?

06:32.783 --> 06:34.219
- You aren't
actually considering

06:34.306 --> 06:35.743
boarding that ship?

06:35.830 --> 06:37.397
I'm an advisor.

06:37.484 --> 06:40.269
I advise you to run away
as fast as you can.

06:40.356 --> 06:43.011
- If we don't figure out how
to disarm that weapon,

06:43.098 --> 06:45.013
there goes our chance
at Starfleet.

06:45.100 --> 06:47.537
If the knowledge on that cube
can help us stop it,

06:47.624 --> 06:49.234
we have to try.

06:49.321 --> 06:51.846
- The Federation's survival
may depend on it.

06:51.933 --> 06:54.762
These readings suggest
the cube is dormant.

06:54.849 --> 06:58.374
Data systems are functional,
but the Borg are sleeping.

06:58.461 --> 07:00.289
- Good.
You see?

07:00.376 --> 07:02.422
We slip in, use their cube
to tell us how to disarm it,

07:02.509 --> 07:03.858
we slip out.

07:03.945 --> 07:05.381
We'll be gone
before they know it,

07:05.468 --> 07:07.383
and we can save Starfleet.

07:07.470 --> 07:09.254
- I'm against this plan,

07:09.341 --> 07:11.343
but if you're going
to be stubborn,

07:11.431 --> 07:14.390
at least let me brief you
on everything I know.

07:14.477 --> 07:17.219
♪ ♪

07:17.306 --> 07:19.351
- Tea.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.615
Black.

07:23.921 --> 07:26.794
- Admiral, you're
not drinking coffee?

07:26.881 --> 07:28.622
- Doctor's orders.

07:28.709 --> 07:32.103
Between you and me, Ensign,
I need a second opinion.

07:32.190 --> 07:35.498
But I know you didn't come here
to talk about beverages.

07:39.894 --> 07:42.374
Dr. Noum, how's our patient?

07:42.462 --> 07:44.725
- He's just coming
out of his stasis.

07:44.812 --> 07:47.292
You're welcome.

07:47.379 --> 07:48.816
- They took my daughter.

07:48.903 --> 07:50.600
- Who took your daughter?

07:50.687 --> 07:53.516
- My mission.

07:53.603 --> 07:55.649
I have to save them.

07:55.736 --> 07:58.216
- Save who?
Can he hear me?

07:58.303 --> 07:59.914
- Not likely,

08:00.001 --> 08:02.394
considering he seemed like
a frozen corpse.

08:02.482 --> 08:05.006
Any sign of life means
I'm a miracle worker.

08:05.093 --> 08:08.183
- We need him awake if we're
going to get any answers.

08:08.270 --> 08:09.924
- Oh, oh, sure.

08:10.011 --> 08:12.143
Let me just wake him up.

08:12.230 --> 08:14.842
Except I don't know his
neurological system functions,

08:14.929 --> 08:17.279
let alone what species he is.

08:17.366 --> 08:20.369
- Admiral, the suit
we found him in

08:20.456 --> 08:23.111
contained some kind
of life sustaining bio serum.

08:23.198 --> 08:25.983
Perhaps, if we replicate it,
we can revive him.

08:26.070 --> 08:30.335
- That's a novel idea,
one of many I've noticed.

08:30.422 --> 08:34.122
- I wish I knew how
to kiss tail like that, Ensign.

08:34.209 --> 08:37.299
Keep it up, and we'll be
taking orders from you.

08:37.386 --> 08:39.388
- How long
until we reach the location

08:39.475 --> 08:41.433
of the last
proto jump signature?

08:41.521 --> 08:43.392
- We should arrive
at relay station 721

08:43.479 --> 08:44.785
in a few hours, Admiral.

08:44.872 --> 08:46.874
- Explore her theory, Doctor.

08:46.961 --> 08:50.312
The sooner he recovers,
the sooner we'll have answers.

08:50.399 --> 08:54.011
♪ ♪

08:54.098 --> 08:57.362
- It seems this cube
went dark for a reason.

08:57.449 --> 09:00.148
A neurolytic pathogen
disabled their nanoprobes

09:00.235 --> 09:02.237
and shut down their drones,

09:02.324 --> 09:05.588
so going in is
still risky but doable.

09:05.675 --> 09:08.548
When in doubt, act harmless,
and you should be ignored,

09:08.635 --> 09:10.637
but please be quick about it.

09:10.724 --> 09:17.600
♪ ♪

09:19.950 --> 09:23.301
- [sighs]
Would you look at this place?

09:23.388 --> 09:25.129
- Spooky.

09:25.216 --> 09:28.089
- Spooky?
It's an engineer's dream.

09:28.176 --> 09:31.309
Carbon tubing?
Thermo couplers?

09:31.396 --> 09:34.704
Ooh, monotanium
aperture valves.

09:34.791 --> 09:37.533
- Oh, now he likes the box.

09:37.620 --> 09:40.667
Jankom, look up.
- [gasps]

09:40.754 --> 09:42.669
- Huh?

09:42.756 --> 09:45.280
♪ ♪

09:45.367 --> 09:46.673
[gasps]

09:46.760 --> 09:54.028
♪ ♪

09:54.855 --> 09:57.771
- And I wouldn't want
to be here when they wake up.

09:57.858 --> 10:04.734
♪ ♪

10:07.128 --> 10:10.348
- Let's just keep moving,
right?

10:10.435 --> 10:13.090
♪ ♪

10:13.177 --> 10:14.875
- This place contains knowledge

10:14.962 --> 10:17.355
of a thousand
assimilated worlds.

10:17.442 --> 10:20.924
We need to find the vinculum
to access it.

10:21.011 --> 10:23.927
Let's hope they have
the intel we need.

10:24.014 --> 10:26.930
♪ ♪

10:27.017 --> 10:29.629
- Which way
to the nerve center?

10:29.716 --> 10:31.369
- This way.

10:31.456 --> 10:33.197
- Oh, great.

10:33.284 --> 10:35.896
The Borg never
assimilated a turbo lift?

10:35.983 --> 10:42.772
♪ ♪

10:42.859 --> 10:44.687
- Ahh!

10:44.774 --> 10:46.384
- Whew.

10:46.471 --> 10:52.303
♪ ♪

10:52.390 --> 10:54.392
- We're nearing
the central data hub.

10:54.479 --> 10:58.092
♪ ♪

10:58.179 --> 11:01.486
- So this is the vinculum
Janeway spoke of.

11:01.573 --> 11:05.186
- All the Borg minds connect
through this hub.

11:05.273 --> 11:08.189
- Wow.
I bet they're super smart.

11:08.276 --> 11:10.060
- Hopefully smart enough
to tell us how

11:10.147 --> 11:12.280
to get that thing off our ship.

11:12.367 --> 11:16.197
- Stand aside and let
Jankom work his hack-gic.

11:16.284 --> 11:18.242
[laughs]

11:18.329 --> 11:21.419
Does anybody see a console?

11:21.506 --> 11:23.726
A keyboard'll do.

11:23.813 --> 11:27.469
Pog can work with a--no,
how about a joystick?

11:27.556 --> 11:28.818
You know what?

11:28.905 --> 11:30.864
Has anybody seen
any buttons whatso--starting

11:30.951 --> 11:32.648
to freak out here.

11:32.735 --> 11:38.480
♪ ♪

11:38.567 --> 11:41.526
- Someone has to plug
themselves into the collective.

11:41.613 --> 11:43.180
♪ ♪

11:47.489 --> 11:49.056
- No one is being assimilated.

11:49.143 --> 11:50.797
- There has to be another way.

11:50.884 --> 11:52.537
- Someone has to link
with the collective

11:52.624 --> 11:53.887
to analyze the weapon.

11:53.974 --> 11:55.018
- Jankom thinks
he speaks for all of us

11:55.105 --> 11:56.628
when he says "not it."

11:56.716 --> 11:58.065
- This isn't a joke.

11:58.152 --> 12:01.111
Whoever goes
in might not come back.

12:01.198 --> 12:02.504
- Eh.
- [clears throat]

12:02.591 --> 12:04.898
- I once belonged
to a collective hive mind.

12:04.985 --> 12:07.378
I know how strong
their hold can be.

12:07.465 --> 12:10.120
If there's anyone who has
a chance at resisting the Borg,

12:10.207 --> 12:11.861
it's me.

12:11.948 --> 12:13.907
[tense music]

12:13.994 --> 12:16.170
- If anything happens that
you don't like, you come out.

12:16.257 --> 12:18.433
You hear me?

12:18.520 --> 12:20.130
- If I succeed,

12:20.217 --> 12:23.568
that weapon will not
harm anyone ever again.

12:23.655 --> 12:25.657
♪ ♪

12:25.745 --> 12:29.400
I promise I will come back.

12:29.487 --> 12:30.488
- Zero!

12:30.575 --> 12:32.360
- Don't get lost in there, Z.

12:32.447 --> 12:35.842
♪ ♪

12:35.929 --> 12:38.148
- Hello, Borg.

12:38.235 --> 12:40.150
My name is Zero.

12:40.237 --> 12:42.283
I know you can hear me.

12:42.370 --> 12:45.939
- Species 802.
Medusan.

12:46.026 --> 12:49.725
There is no "I."
There is only Borg.

12:49.812 --> 12:53.990
- You're not harmed
by my appearance?

12:54.077 --> 12:56.297
It has been known
to hurt others.

12:56.384 --> 12:59.691
- Here in the vinculum,
you cannot hurt us.

12:59.779 --> 13:02.129
Your uniqueness is
acknowledged here.

13:02.216 --> 13:04.871
Your distinctiveness
will be added to our own.

13:04.958 --> 13:07.351
- Oh, dear.
Aren't you a chatty bunch?

13:07.438 --> 13:10.354
I forgot what it's like
to share a hive mind.

13:10.441 --> 13:14.402
It's so overwhelming.

13:14.489 --> 13:16.752
♪ ♪

13:16.839 --> 13:19.189
- [gasps]
They're scanning our ship.

13:19.276 --> 13:21.539
Crew, what's going
on over there?

13:21.626 --> 13:24.934
Status report.

13:25.021 --> 13:27.589
Whatever you're doing,
the Borg are waking up.

13:27.676 --> 13:30.244
You need to hurry.

13:30.331 --> 13:33.116
[machinery clanking
and whirring]

13:33.203 --> 13:39.819
♪ ♪

13:46.260 --> 13:47.870
- Why are they waking up?

13:47.957 --> 13:49.872
Jankom thinks this looks bad.

13:49.959 --> 13:51.134
- Oh, no.

13:51.221 --> 13:52.875
They're already
inside Zero's mind.

13:52.962 --> 13:54.703
- Wake up, Z!
Wake up!

13:54.790 --> 13:56.705
- Janeway, tell me you
can beam us out of here.

13:56.792 --> 13:58.794
- The cube's defenses
are interfering.

13:58.881 --> 14:00.143
You'll have
to find another way out.

14:00.230 --> 14:03.320
- Ah!
- Ah!

14:03.407 --> 14:04.800
- We have to go.

14:04.887 --> 14:07.107
- We can't just leave Zero!

14:07.194 --> 14:09.152
♪ ♪

14:09.239 --> 14:12.112
- Resistance is futile.

14:12.199 --> 14:14.244
♪ ♪

14:14.331 --> 14:16.943
- We'll come back for Z.
Come on!

14:17.030 --> 14:23.297
♪ ♪

14:23.384 --> 14:26.561
all: Ah!

14:26.648 --> 14:28.345
- You will be assimilated.

14:28.432 --> 14:30.695
- Eh, I'm good.

14:30.782 --> 14:32.872
♪ ♪

14:32.959 --> 14:36.005
Ah, they're not so tough.

14:36.092 --> 14:39.704
♪ ♪

14:39.791 --> 14:42.620
- They adapted to our phasers!

14:42.707 --> 14:44.405
- Let's see how
they adapt to this.

14:44.492 --> 14:47.321
[grunting]

14:47.408 --> 14:49.192
- Gwyn, behind you!

14:49.279 --> 14:51.978
♪ ♪

14:52.065 --> 14:54.589
Keep changing
the phase variance!

14:54.676 --> 15:01.335
♪ ♪

15:01.422 --> 15:02.727
- Whoa!

15:02.814 --> 15:04.555
Uh-oh.
- Whoa!

15:04.642 --> 15:08.298
♪ ♪

15:08.385 --> 15:11.258
- [grunting]

15:11.345 --> 15:12.607
- [laughs]

15:12.694 --> 15:14.826
♪ ♪

15:14.914 --> 15:17.177
Back off!

15:17.264 --> 15:24.140
♪ ♪

15:26.795 --> 15:30.712
Uh, they destroyed the bridge!

15:30.799 --> 15:32.583
- No, no, no.

15:32.670 --> 15:39.808
♪ ♪

15:47.120 --> 15:48.469
- Dal!

15:48.556 --> 15:50.036
- Get out of here.

15:50.123 --> 15:51.646
Save Zero!

15:51.733 --> 15:53.735
Don't make it easy for them!

15:53.822 --> 15:58.479
♪ ♪

15:58.566 --> 16:00.437
- There's no need to hide.

16:00.524 --> 16:02.309
Give yourself over.

16:02.396 --> 16:04.006
Become one of us.

16:04.093 --> 16:06.226
- I can't.

16:06.313 --> 16:07.749
There is a weapon
aboard our ship.

16:07.836 --> 16:10.708
- The Living Construct.

16:10.795 --> 16:12.797
- Yes!
I need your help.

16:12.884 --> 16:16.714
- It is a destructive force
and a danger to the Federation.

16:16.801 --> 16:18.107
- If it can
hurt the Federation,

16:18.194 --> 16:19.979
one day,
it could hurt the Borg.

16:20.066 --> 16:23.765
We must deactivate it, but how?

16:23.852 --> 16:26.855
- We will assimilate the ship
and use the Living Construct

16:26.942 --> 16:28.596
to assimilate our enemies.

16:28.683 --> 16:30.119
- No!

16:30.206 --> 16:31.468
That's not what we--I mean,
what I want.

16:31.555 --> 16:34.994
Tell me how to deactivate
the Living Construct.

16:35.081 --> 16:36.560
- Irrelevant.

16:36.647 --> 16:40.129
Your crew will be assimilated
to advance the Borg.

16:40.216 --> 16:42.479
- No, no.

16:42.566 --> 16:44.481
- Resistance is futile.

16:44.568 --> 16:51.532
♪ ♪

16:51.619 --> 16:53.664
- Dal?
Rok?

16:53.751 --> 16:55.014
Is anyone there?

16:55.101 --> 16:58.756
- They've all been captured.

16:58.843 --> 17:01.498
You don't have long until
the Borg assimilate them.

17:01.585 --> 17:02.978
It's up to you, Gwyn.

17:03.065 --> 17:05.328
- No, I have to get to Zero.

17:05.415 --> 17:07.243
Zero can tell them
to let us go.

17:07.330 --> 17:08.984
- Remember what I told you.

17:09.071 --> 17:11.769
If you're not a threat,
they will ignore you.

17:11.856 --> 17:13.119
Lay down your weapon.

17:13.206 --> 17:15.425
- How will I defend myself?

17:15.512 --> 17:17.210
- Gwyn, trust me.

17:17.297 --> 17:19.255
Stand down.

17:19.342 --> 17:21.518
- Nice tip, Janeway.

17:21.605 --> 17:28.482
♪ ♪

17:50.199 --> 17:55.378
Dal?

17:56.597 --> 18:00.644
[tense music]

18:00.731 --> 18:02.516
both: Gwyn!

18:02.603 --> 18:04.909
- Get us out of here!

18:04.996 --> 18:06.781
♪ ♪

18:06.868 --> 18:08.435
Zero, great.

18:08.522 --> 18:09.740
- Uh, Zero?

18:09.827 --> 18:13.004
[ominous beeping]

18:13.092 --> 18:15.703
- Resistance is futile.

18:15.790 --> 18:18.140
- What did they do to you?

18:18.227 --> 18:21.100
- Apparently gave Z
a new set of mitts.

18:21.187 --> 18:24.581
Nobody offered Pog upgrades.

18:24.668 --> 18:27.367
Actually, Jankom will pass
on the upgrades.

18:27.454 --> 18:33.286
♪ ♪

18:33.373 --> 18:36.202
Uh...

18:36.289 --> 18:38.204
No haircut.
Zero!

18:38.291 --> 18:39.553
No haircut!

18:39.640 --> 18:41.076
Ah!

18:41.163 --> 18:42.860
- Fight the collective, Zero.

18:42.947 --> 18:44.862
- There is no Zero.

18:44.949 --> 18:47.169
Zero hurt you.

18:47.256 --> 18:49.345
Endangered you.

18:49.432 --> 18:52.783
Now Zero is Borg.

18:52.870 --> 18:54.872
- Well, the Borg are
making you hurt us,

18:54.959 --> 18:57.092
and that is
not the Zero I know.

18:57.179 --> 19:00.574
- Ahh, ahh!

19:00.661 --> 19:05.535
- We will not hurt
others anymore.

19:05.622 --> 19:07.711
- Good, good, good.
It's working.

19:07.798 --> 19:11.411
- We will assimilate you
into the collective.

19:11.498 --> 19:13.282
- No, no, no!

19:13.369 --> 19:15.197
- Bad Zero, bad Zero!

19:15.284 --> 19:16.894
- We all get hurt, Zero.

19:16.981 --> 19:19.070
It's the risk we take
for revealing pieces

19:19.158 --> 19:20.463
of ourselves to each other,

19:20.550 --> 19:23.118
but what you did,
trying to protect me,

19:23.205 --> 19:24.554
was an act of love,

19:24.641 --> 19:26.774
and you should never
feel ashamed for that.

19:26.861 --> 19:29.168
If there's any part
still listening,

19:29.255 --> 19:31.039
protect us again, Zero.

19:31.126 --> 19:33.607
Break free from their hold.
- [screaming]

19:33.694 --> 19:37.480
- Resistance is not futile.

19:37.567 --> 19:43.269
- Resistance is not futile?

19:43.356 --> 19:46.097
[Borg whispering indistinctly]

19:46.185 --> 19:50.580
- I will resist because I'm
already a part of a collective

19:50.667 --> 19:53.931
that is stronger
than you will ever be!

19:54.018 --> 20:00.938
♪ ♪

20:08.816 --> 20:11.427
Friends, are you all right?
We must hurry.

20:11.514 --> 20:12.863
I lured them
into a dormant state,

20:12.950 --> 20:14.038
but it won't hold for long.

20:14.125 --> 20:16.302
- Zero's back!

20:16.389 --> 20:17.955
- I thought we lost you.

20:18.042 --> 20:20.567
[soft music]

20:20.654 --> 20:23.700
- I've already
found my collective.

20:23.787 --> 20:25.920
- Yeah, yeah.
That's great.

20:26.007 --> 20:28.052
Now help us out of here.

20:28.139 --> 20:32.013
♪ ♪

20:32.100 --> 20:33.971
- Crew, do you read?
Get back to the ship.

20:34.058 --> 20:35.625
Follow my signal.

20:35.712 --> 20:42.632
♪ ♪

20:42.719 --> 20:44.330
Let's go.

20:44.417 --> 20:46.332
I've had enough Borg
for two lifetimes.

20:46.419 --> 20:52.120
♪ ♪

20:52.207 --> 20:53.948
- After everything
we went through,

20:54.035 --> 20:55.515
what did you learn from them?

20:55.602 --> 20:57.647
- When they analyzed
the Living Construct

20:57.734 --> 21:00.824
the Borg determined
it sadly cannot

21:00.911 --> 21:04.785
be deactivated or removed.

21:04.872 --> 21:07.570
- You're saying
we can't shut it off.

21:07.657 --> 21:09.311
- But at least
we know a little more.

21:09.398 --> 21:12.662
- We have Zero back,
and that's enough for me.

21:12.749 --> 21:15.361
- And you survived the Borg.

21:15.448 --> 21:17.493
Consider me impressed.

21:17.580 --> 21:20.757
- Zero, how did you
escape the Borg hive mind?

21:20.844 --> 21:24.283
- I listened to a friend.

21:24.370 --> 21:27.286
While I may have harmed others
in the past,

21:27.373 --> 21:30.550
I now choose to save.

21:30.637 --> 21:33.117
The same is true for our ship.

21:33.204 --> 21:35.598
It may be a weapon
against Starfleet,

21:35.685 --> 21:38.949
but it can still
be used for good.

21:39.036 --> 21:42.779
- So we're not going
to Starfleet?

21:42.866 --> 21:45.608
- Not until we can
get there safely.

21:45.695 --> 21:48.394
- But they can tell
you who you are.

21:48.481 --> 21:50.744
- The answer will
always be there.

21:50.831 --> 21:53.050
It just might take us
a little longer.

21:53.137 --> 21:55.618
[computer beeping]

21:55.705 --> 21:59.492
- A distress signal?
[gasps]

21:59.579 --> 22:00.884
Can we help?
Can we help?

22:00.971 --> 22:02.364
Can we help?
- What do you think?

22:02.451 --> 22:05.149
Five minds are better than one.

22:05.236 --> 22:08.805
- [squeaks]
- I stand corrected, 5 1/2.

22:08.892 --> 22:10.894
- We may not be ready
for Starfleet,

22:10.981 --> 22:13.462
but we're ready to take
your orders, Captain.

22:13.549 --> 22:15.551
- Then let's do some good.

22:15.638 --> 22:16.944
Plot a course.

22:17.031 --> 22:19.033
- Yeah.

22:19.120 --> 22:22.036
[exciting music]

22:22.123 --> 22:26.475
♪ ♪

22:26.562 --> 22:28.782
- You're growing and adapting.

22:28.869 --> 22:31.437
- Eh, what can I say?

22:31.524 --> 22:33.569
Resistance is futile.

22:33.656 --> 22:38.792
♪ ♪

22:38.879 --> 22:43.362
- Admiral's log,
stardate 61284.3.

22:43.449 --> 22:45.712
We arrived at CR 721

22:45.799 --> 22:48.018
only to make
a frightening discovery,

22:48.105 --> 22:52.414
a helpless Starfleet
relay station decimated.

22:52.501 --> 22:54.329
No sign of survivors.

22:54.416 --> 22:57.245
The Captain Chakotay
I know could never do this.

22:57.332 --> 23:00.117
I fear he's lost command
of the Protostar,

23:00.204 --> 23:04.252
and whoever gave this order
must be stopped.

23:04.339 --> 23:07.211
[dramatic music]

23:07.298 --> 23:13.087
♪ ♪

23:13.174 --> 23:17.483
- [gasps]

23:17.570 --> 23:24.490
♪ ♪
